events.name: Los Angeles Lakers at Charlotte Hornets

headlines.description: — Anthony Davis had 42 points and 23 rebounds, and the Los Angeles Lakers used a huge first quarter from the All-Star center to build a 23-point lead before beating the Charlotte Hornets 112-107 on Monday night for their fourth straight win.
headlines.shortLinkText: Anthony Davis scores 42 points, grabs 23 rebounds as Lakers top Hornets 112-107 for 4th straight win

headlines.description: — Darius Garland scored 22 points, Donovan Mitchell added 21 and the Cleveland Cavaliers snapped a season-high, three-game losing streak with a 110-91 win over the Detroit Pistons on Monday night.
headlines.shortLinkText: Darius Garland scores 22, Donovan Mitchell 21 as Cavs end mini slide with 110-91 win over Pistons

headlines.description: — Amen Thompson hit a game-winning floater with 0.7 seconds left and finished with 33 points to lead the Houston Rockets to a 114-112 victory over the Boston Celtics on Monday night.
headlines.shortLinkText: Thompson hits game-winning shot and scores 33 points as Rockets rally past Celtics 114-112

headlines.description: — Domantas Sabonis had 21 points, 22 rebounds and 10 assists in his seventh triple-double of the season, De’Aaron Fox scored 30 points and the Sacramento Kings beat the Brooklyn Nets 110-96 on Monday night.
headlines.shortLinkText: Sabonis grabs 22 rebounds in another triple-double as Kings beat Nets 110-96

headlines.description: — Tyler Herro scored 30 points, Bam Adebayo finished with 26 and the Miami Heat erased a 14-point deficit in the fourth quarter before beating the Orlando Magic 125-119 in double overtime on Monday night.
headlines.shortLinkText: Heat, playing without Butler, get 30 from Herro and top Magic 125-119 in double overtime

events.name: Memphis Grizzlies at New York Knicks

headlines.description: — Mikal Bridges had 28 points, six assists and five rebounds, and the New York Knicks snapped the Memphis Grizzlies’ six-game winning streak with a resounding 143-106 win on Monday night.
headlines.shortLinkText: Knicks surpass 140 for second straight game, snap Grizzlies' 6-game win streak with 143-106 rout

events.name: New Orleans Pelicans at Toronto Raptors

headlines.description: — Jakob Poeltl had 21 points and 14 rebounds, Scottie Barnes had 21 points and 11 boards, and the Toronto Raptors beat the New Orleans Pelicans 113-104 on Monday night for their first four-game winning streak in almost two years.
headlines.shortLinkText: Poeltl, Barnes lead Raptors past Pelicans 113-104 for Toronto's first 4-game win streak since 2023

headlines.description: — Nikola Vucevic had 20 points, 10 rebounds and six assists, and the Chicago Bulls handed the Denver Nuggets their second straight loss with a 129-121 victory on Monday night.
headlines.shortLinkText: Vucevic helps the Bulls hold off Jokic and the Nuggets for a 129-121 victory

headlines.description: — Anthony Edwards scored 23 points and Julius Randle added 20 to help the Minnesota Timberwolves hold off the short-handed Atlanta Hawks...
headlines.shortLinkText: Timberwolves fend off depleted Hawks 100-92 despite DeAndre Hunter's career-high 35 points

headlines.description: — Klay Thompson scored 21 of his 23 points in the first quarter, matching a Dallas record by hitting seven 3-pointers in the period, and the Mavericks breezed past the NBA-worst Washington Wizards 130-108 on Monday night.
headlines.shortLinkText: Klay Thompson makes 7 3s in 1st quarter as Mavs breeze past NBA-worst Wizards 130-108

headlines.description: — Giannis Antetokounmpo and Damian Lillard each scored 35 points to lead the Milwaukee Bucks to a 125-110 victory over the Utah Jazz on Monday night.
headlines.shortLinkText: Antetokounmpo and Lillard both score 35 as Bucks roll past Jazz 125-110

headlines.description: — Devin Booker scored 26 points, Kevin Durant added 24 and the surging Phoenix Suns survived a late scare for a 111-109 win over the Los Angeles Clippers on Monday night.
headlines.shortLinkText: Devin Booker scores 26 and the Suns survive a late scare to beat the Clippers 111-109
